# Content Guidelines

Guidelines for writing and formatting documentation in this project.

## Writing Style

- Use clear, concise language
- Write in a conversational tone
- Use active voice when possible
- Break complex information into smaller chunks
- Use headings and subheadings to organize content

## Formatting

- Use Markdown for all documentation files
- Follow a consistent heading structure (H1 → H2 → H3)
- Use bullet points for lists of items
- Use numbered lists for sequential steps
- Include code examples with proper syntax highlighting

## Images and Assets

- Store images in the [static/img/](mdc:static/img) directory
- Use descriptive filenames for images
- Include alt text for accessibility
- Optimize images for web (compress when possible)
- Use screenshots to illustrate UI elements

## Code Examples

- Include complete, working code examples when possible
- Use appropriate language syntax highlighting
- Add comments to explain complex parts
- Format code consistently
- Test all code examples before adding them to documentation
